DURING THE INITIAL CLIMB AT THE BEGINNING OF AN AERIAL APPLICATION 
FLIGHT, THE PILOT MADE A CLIMBING 180 DEGREE RIGHT TURN IN THE REVERSE 
DIRECTION WHEN THE ROTOR RPM BEGAN TO DROP. THE PILOT CONTINUED TO 
RAISE COLLECTIVE, LOST DIRECTIONAL CONTROL AND COLLIDED WITH THE 
TERRAIN APPROXIMATELY 100 YARDS FROM THE INITIAL LIFT-OFF POINT. THE 
REASON FOR THE POWER LOSS WAS NOT DETERMINED. 
